### Instruction:
in a javascript web app, how do you save text to a local file

### Response:

To save text to a local file in JavaScript, you can use the following code: 

```javascript
// Create a new Blob object with the text as its data
var blob = new Blob([text], {type:"text/plain"});

// Convert the Blob object into a File object
var file = new File(blob, "filename.txt");

// Trigger a save dialog to prompt user for a location to save the file
navigator.fileManger.saveAs(file);
```
